&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://thisisnthappiness.com/&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;This Isn’t Happiness&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; class=&quot;external-icon&quot; style=&quot;max-width:0.8em;max-height:0.8em&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (added 2025-05-01)&lt;/p&gt;

 &lt;p&gt;Boy oh boy are people going to be upset when they find out — as they surely will — that DOGE’s übermunchkins are in up your data deleting everything in sight to make restoring these institutions impossible. &lt;em&gt;Or do you doubt Musk would think of that?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For a while now I’ve been telling people not to waste their time or distract others with bullshit about the inner life of fascists. Now that Actual, Certifiable Nazis have taken over the USG, that takes on a new dimension. But I’ve been saying for a long time because that manufactured space of intention is how they’ve gotten off in the media (“just kidding”) and courts (“but did he really &lt;em&gt;know&lt;/em&gt; or &lt;em&gt;mean&lt;/em&gt; x, y, z”?). But if you take away that imaginary space away, you’re left with the empirical evidence of what they say and do — and can prosecute them for it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, to look ahead a bit, if non-fascists ever gain power again (very much TBD), they’ll need to prosecute Musk’s shocktwerps. Courts will lavish aaaalll kinds of attention on whether they &lt;em&gt;really knew&lt;/em&gt; that wanton, systematic destruction of govt records was illegal. Fuck that. I don’t car whether Mr. BigBallz imagined his fingers crossed behind his back when he took an oath. What they’re doing is wildly illegal AND THEY KNOW IT — hence all the secrecy, the strategic ambiguity, the games about who they are, what their title and status is, where the orders came from, etc, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So: If you want this mess to be fixed as much as possible and the culprits to be held to maximal account, that’s another reason — as I say — to NOT WASTE THEIR TIME OR DISTRACT OTHERS WITH BULLSH*T ABOUT THE INNER LIFE OF FASCISTS.&lt;/p&gt;

 &lt;p&gt;Now that Trump &amp;#x26; Co. have made it clear they’re coming after Harvard too, it’s worth sharing &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/tbyfield/posts/pfbid0248ppuY7AemQ1BMidPRDTBfpW8uduqVoiVbW4nB2A7b55CcGFSwBpm2WpreUgqPG8l&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;this squib I posted on Facebook last week&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; class=&quot;external-icon&quot; style=&quot;max-width:0.8em;max-height:0.8em&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (with a few edits and context):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So many pseudo-sophisticates are saying “Columbia has $14B, they should just [fill in the blank].” People, &lt;em&gt;please.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Very little of that asset base is liquid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Huge amounts of it come with strict contractual limits on how it can be used — and asking donors to revise those agreements carries its own risks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lots of it is &lt;em&gt;promised&lt;/em&gt; rather than in hand&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spending down their endowment won’t actually solve the problem, which is that the president of the US wants to make an example of the school, and has many more tools for doing so.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If they did it, a lot of other schools would go ballistic, particularly those that &lt;em&gt;aren’t&lt;/em&gt; wealthy — and the leftish peanut gallery would join right in, railing about inequity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
